problem:
Find the value of $a$ so that the lines with the given equations are perpendicular. \begin{align*}
y &= 2x+13 \\
6y+ax &= 6.
\end{align*}

steps:
For the lines to be perpendicular, the product of their slopes must be -1. Therefore, \begin{align*}
\left(2\right)\left(\frac{-a}{6}\right) &=-1 \\
\frac{-2a}{6} &=-1
\end{align*}

